# The Superlative Podcast — Project Overview

## What This Is
A minimal, content-driven podcast landing page for **The Superlative Podcast**, hosted by **Edward Buchi** (@thespeakerlisan), co-founder of Sacred Protocol. Episodes are 20–30 minute live conversations with founders, investors, and operators. No edits, no post-production. Streamed live to X and YouTube.

## Stack
- **Next.js 16.2.2** (App Router) — note: breaking changes from older Next.js versions. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before touching framework-level code.
- **React 19.2.4**
- **Tailwind CSS v4** (PostCSS plugin, not the v3 config file approach)
- **TypeScript 5** (strict mode)

## Key Files
| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/config.ts` | Single source of truth — all episodes, site links, host info |
| `src/app/page.tsx` | Entire site — all 6 sections as inline functions |
| `src/app/layout.tsx` | Fonts (Geist + Special Gothic), metadata, OG image |
| `src/app/globals.css` | Design tokens, animations, section spacing utilities |
| `src/components/XPostEmbed.tsx` | Twitter/X post embed (client component) |
| `src/components/XTimelineEmbed.tsx` | Twitter/X timeline embed (client component) |
| `public/og-image.png` | Open Graph image for link previews |
| `public/favicon.png` | TSP branded favicon |

## Site Sections (in order)
1. **Hero** — Full-height, animated title + tagline + CTAs (booking + YouTube)
2. **Episodes** — Full episode list with platform pill badges (X / YouTube)
3. **About** — Blurb, follow button, format descriptor
4. **GuestVerticals** — 4-column grid (Startups, Media, Sports, Finance)
5. **CTABanner** — Guest booking call-to-action
6. **Footer** — Copyright, social links (X, YouTube, booking)

